{
  "texts": [
    "We will cover some of the existing research on gender bias in both neural MT systems (Section 3.1) and more recent work focusing on GPT models used as MT systems (Section 3.2).",
    "NMT models are typically bidirectional sequence-to-sequence (seq2seq) (Sutskever et al., 2014) architectures with encoder-decoder frameworks while GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) models are primary a language models for language generation tasks.",
    "Both the more commonly employed NMT systems (the type of model used by Google Translate 7, DeepL 8, and others.)",
    "and GPT models are based on Transformers (Vaswani et al., 2017).",
    "However, GPT models are decoder-only models as opposed to the usual encoder-decoder architectures of the conventional MT systems."
  ]
}